const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can the AI assess installations from photos?",
    answer: "A driveway photograph shows the mounting position and approximate cable route but cannot determine the supply type, consumer unit capacity, earth electrode resistance, or internal cable run through walls and floors. The AI uses photos constructively — noting the wall material for bracket fixing, the visible distance from the proposed charger position to the meter cupboard, and whether the driveway surface would require trenching — building a pre-survey brief so you arrive knowing the external layout and likely SWA route."
  },
  {
    question: "What about multi-message EV threads?",
    answer: "EV conversations develop across multiple messages — a homeowner sends a driveway photo, then confirms the car is a Mercedes EQA, then asks about Easee vs Wallbox, then mentions Octopus Agile tariff, then queries the OZEV grant, then requests Wednesday installation. The AI builds one integrated lead from every fragment: driveway layout, vehicle model, brand comparison, smart tariff, grant eligibility, and preferred installation date."
